{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"agent_message","text":"The failure path is now clearer: the changed-metadata matrix can emit coordinates from `index.json` diffs even when those coordinates are not resolvable by the TCK because the metadata directory for the mapped `metadata-version` is missing. That makes `run-consecutive-tests` schedule work that `tckClean` is guaranteed to reject. I’m checking the current diff and the matrix generation path to keep the fix scoped to that gate instead of broadening coordinate semantics globally."}}
